  "title": "DRAFTER",
  "description": "<p><strong>Drafter</strong></p>\n<p>(Building Construction/Project)</p>\n<p>Responsibilities :</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Liaise with builders and contractors to create and update plans, drawings for building projects.</li>\n  <li>Work closely with architects, engineers and construction teams to integrate design elements and ensure coordination across disciplines.</li>\n  <li>Responsible for creating detailed and technical drawings based on sketches and instructions provided by the site/design team</li>\n  <li>Develop comprehensive construction drawings, adhering to local building codes and regulations.</li>\n  <li>Gather product and structural requirements, calculating dimensions and material specifications, and creating detailed designs using computer-aided design (CAD) software.</li>\n  <li>Prepare preliminary sketches, working drawings and detailed specifications.</li>\n  <li>Monitor the construction process to ensure works aligns with the approved drawings and specifications.</li>\n  <li>Any other works as assigned by the Management or your Superior.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Requirements :</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Bachelor’s Degree of Architecture/Drafting/Engineering Design or other related disciplines</li>\n  <li>A firm foundation in drawing creation – BIM, Revit, Navisworks, Sketch-up, AutoCad software / computer-aided design (CAD) and general computer skills.</li>\n  <li>Previous work experiences in a specific industry, such as architectural, mechanical, or structural design, will require to be considered for the position.</li>\n  <li>Minimum 2 years of experience in building/construction trade in Singapore will be added advantage.</li>\n</ul>",
